# Backend Conventions

## Structure

- `app/` — core: models, schemas, database config
- `routers/` — REST routes, one file per resource, kept thin
- `websocket/` — WebSocket signaling layer

## Patterns

- Business logic in service functions — route handlers only wire inputs to outputs
- Dependency injection via `get_db()` for per-request DB sessions
- Pydantic v2 schemas with `ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)` for ORM serialization
- SQLAlchemy 2 declarative models in `app/models.py`
- Use `HTTPException` with appropriate status codes; no bare `except`
- Package managed with `uv`; Python 3.12
